    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored today by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (78.72), our clear elite starts. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a high-ceiling matchup against Roupp, bolstered by a significant +16% park factor and the high-leverage leadoff spot. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** is positioned to capitalize on a favorable wind-out environment against Kumar Rocker, with his high xwOBA suggesting he is primed for a multi-hit performance. **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) also grades out as a top-tier play, as his efficiency is boosted significantly by a +17% SP skill advantage against Tomoyuki Sugano, making him a critical component of our offensive output today.\n\nWhile we are optimized for efficiency, the bench remains a point of contention. **Nolan Schanuel** (47.94) came closest to cracking the starting lineup, but was ultimately squeezed out due to a difficult matchup against Corbin Burnes and a high rain risk (38%) that threatens his availability. We are closely monitoring the weather in that matchup, as well as the status of **Miguel Vargas** (51.95), who faces a 31% rain risk against Bubic. Despite the volatility, we continue to prioritize stolen base potential\u2014even in suboptimal matchups\u2014which is why **Nasim Nunez** (45.03) remains in the lineup despite a tough draw against the elite Aaron Ashby (2.89 xERA). His ability to exploit the slow delivery of Ashby remains our primary hedge in the scarcest category of the 5x5 format.\n\nInvestors should note that several slots\u2014including **Liam Hicks**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages**\u2014are still based on pending lineup confirmations. While we have utilized historical projections for these spots, any late-scratch or order-shift will require immediate re-evaluation of the 5x5 scoring ceiling. We are comfortable holding **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** on the bench today, as both projected below our current starters in raw efficiency, allowing us to maintain our strategic focus on high-probability contact and speed-based scoring potential.",
